Thank you for including that in your work. It's like an Easter Egg hunt. I try do it myself. I also try not to make it so obscure that only one of a hundred find it, but I do deliberately try to lay it out so that even when most people find something extra, they each find their own version of it. One of the greatest rewards I get is when people see something I didn't intend and I get surprised by the implications of my own work that I missed. And, I don't mean when I make a mistake that is embarrassing or needs correction, I mean when a whole new vista of possibilities arise that give me new territory to explore. I lead people to a forest of many paths, then let them explore it and report back on their experiences.

Any chance there will be more leopard girl stalker? I'm fascinated by the world she would live in where that is maybe a bit odd, but also "normal" behavior as expected from different species.

There's a 50% chance that you get to meet your waifur, and a 50% chance that you will end.

If you make the first 50% and actually meet your waifur, there is then a 50% chance it won't work and a 50% chance that it will.

That's a 75% chance that your suffering will end, but a 25% chance that your suffering will become even worse. And, over all, a 25% chance that you will have a happy ending with a loving waifur.

I'll take those odds. Rollin' right now:
0-4 - universe ends, suffering ends
5-7 - find my waifur, but she rejects me
8-9, all dubbs, tripps, etc. (negates singles above) - forever happiness with perfect waifur

Wish me luck, lads.
